import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Data
data = {
    'Year': [1438, 1525, 1528, 1536, 1500, 1520, 1530, 1565, 1470, 1475, 1472, 1480, 1477, 1474, 1476, 1479, 1483, 1585, 1600, 1583, 1550, 2000, 1806, 1784, 1785, 1788, 1793, 1840, 1824, 1771, 1764, 1811, 1770, 1856, 1879, 1799, 1787, 1814, 1862, 1827, 1789, 1800],

}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)

# Group by year and find the minimum number of swords
min_swords_per_year = df.groupby('Year')['Number of Swords'].min()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
plt.plot(min_swords_per_year.index, min_swords_per_year.values, marker='o')
plt.title('Lowest Number of Swords Depicted Each Year')
plt.xlabel('Year')
plt.ylabel('Number of Swords')
plt.grid(True)
plt.savefig('/home/ubuntu/workspace/XMODE-LLMCompiler/ceasura_langgraph/experiments/log/14/plot-out.png')
